      "id": "PopularPost108717",
      "post_content": "Here's this card should have been:  \n  \n{B}{B} Enchantment (*not* enchant creature)  \n  \n{B}{B}{B}{B}: put a -1/-1 counter on target creature.  \n  \nThis way you have a reliable and recurring, yet aggressive method of killing those creatures out of reach of terrors or dark banishings.   \n  \nAs it is, you will just stop your opponent from attacking with that creature. They can still block, which can be a big pain if you're trying to sneak your hypnotic specter around a pro-black flier.  \n  \nAlso -0/-2 counters are stupid and make calculating power and toughness needlessly complex.",
      "posted_by": "allmighty_abacus",
